    • Constructor Detail

      • SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive

        public SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive()
        Default constructor. Equivalent to FixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive(null).

        An instance of FixMarketMirror is used as underlying mirror.

      • SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive

        public SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive(FIXVersion defaultFixVersion)
        Constructor which allows you to set a default FIX version.

        An instance of FixMarketMirror is used as underlying mirror.

        Parameters:
        defaultFixVersion - FIX version to use if it can't be extracted from the messages. The FIX version is needed to correctly populate the OrdStatus tag (39) on the original order after a Cancel/Replace message. It could come from the session owning this mirror for example.

      • SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive

        public SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive(IMarketMirror mirror,
                                                   IOrderArchive archive)
        Convenience constructor for creating a mirror programmatically (rather than by configuration) in client code.
        Parameters:
        mirror - the underlying in-memory mirror
        archive - the order archive

      • SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive

        public SynchronizedFixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive(IMarketMirror mirror,
                                                   IArchiveLog archiveLog,
                                                   String dictionaryName)
        Convenience constructor for creating a mirror programmatically (rather than by configuration) in client code.

        This constructor will use OrderArchiveLog as IOrderArchive. So essentially it is the same as calling new FixMarketMirrorWithOrderArchive(mirror, new OrderArchiveLog(archiveLog, mirror, dictionaryName))

        Parameters:
        mirror - the underlying in-memory mirror
        archiveLog - an IArchiveLog to use as underlying storage for the archive
        dictionaryName - used when creating an OrderArchiveLog, is used when order record is deserialized

      • configure

        public void configure(IConfiguration configuration)
               throws ConfigurationException
        Description copied from interface: IConfigurable
        Apply the IConfiguration to this IConfigurable.

        This method is called by the configuration module in the server:

        • when loading the configuration at server startup (e.g. when reading the XML configuration file) and
        • every time we reload the configuration object corresponding to the configurable run-time object.
        The Catalys Server passes a reference to a configuration clone. The original reference is unavailable to the configurable object. The configurable object may decide to store the reference as the last valid configuration object which can be used to optimize the re-configuration.
        Specified by:
        configure in interface IConfigurable
        Parameters:
        configuration - the immutable configuration object
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - This exception is thrown when the new configuration object cannot be applied to the configurable object.
